# Branding your service

You need to make sure the service uses the right header, footer and typeface for where it’s being provided, or you risk confusing users.

Your site must look like GOV.UK if it’s on one of the following domains:

- gov.uk/myservice
- myservice.service.gov.uk
- myblog.blog.gov.uk


You should follow the guidance on the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/service-manual/design/making-your-service-look-like-govuk" target="_blank" rel="noopner noreferrer">GOV.UK Service Manual for making the service look like GOV.UK (opens in new tab)</a>

